The Vice President, Mike Pence, gave a speech at the Williamsburg Tourism and Convention Center in Williamsburg, Kentucky, thanking Governor Matt Bevin and First Lady Glenna for their partnership with the Trump administration. Pence highlighted the achievements of the Trump administration, including tax cuts, cutting red tape, supporting American energy independence, and rebuilding the military. He also expressed gratitude to Congressman Hal Rogers for his service and support. Pence emphasized the administration's commitment to law enforcement and thanked the men and women in uniform for their service, acknowledging the sacrifices they and their families make. He praised Governor Bevin for his partnership in upholding the rule of law and securing the southern border. Pence concluded by urging support for Bevin's reelection and assuring the audience that the administration stands with them in defending their communities and the nation.